condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Schedule 2/Section I./B1. | Description :The Recipient will maintain throughout Project implementation the PSC,JTWG and BH PCU with adequate staff and resources to manage all aspects of Project implementation. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2/Section I./B2. | Description :The Entities will maintain throughout Project implementation the FBiHPCU and RS PCU with adequate staff and resources to manage all aspects of Project implementation | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2/Section I./B3. | Description :The Recipient shall, and cause the Entities to, adopt a staffing planfor the restructuring of MoFTER, the FBiH MoAWMF, and the RS MoAFWM on terms and conditions satisfactory to the Association. | DueDate :16-Apr-2010

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2/Section I./B4. | Description :The Recipient shall cause the FBiH to establish the FBiH AgricultureExtension Services Agency, in a manner and with the composition and terms of reference satisfactory to the Association | Due Date:16-Apr-2010

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2/Section I./B5. | Description :The Recipient, through MoFTER and the BH PCU, shall duly perform allits obligations under the Operational Manual and the EMF. | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2/Section I./B6 | Description :The Recipient shall cause the Entities, through the FBiH MoAWMF/RSMoAFWM and the FBiH PCU/RS PCU to duly perform all their obligations under the OM, FM Manual, RD Grants Manual, and EMF. | Due Date:16-Apr-2010

title.narrative: Transparent Entity level paying systems established
Entity level rural development plans established and overseen by Monitoring Committees
APPH implementing plant health monitoring and risk assessment

baseline.value: APPH only recently established and not fullystaffed or operational

target.value: 80% of seed and plant material producers/importers are registered.- potato pest survey repeated yearly

actual.value: Phyto register in use by inspection services, border control and pest identification manual printed and distributed.

title.narrative: RS MAFWM/FBiH MAWMF agricultural information units and databases and FADN pilot established assembling farm level information

baseline.value: Adhoc record keeping and no M&E for formulation of policy for support programs

target.value: Integrate FADN survey data in entity MoA information system

actual.value: Operational in RS with FADN pilot sample of 113 farms. FBiH not functioning, data collection at cantonal level not agreed andlacking financial resources. To be resolved as part of the new extension legislation. RS in collaboration with MOFTER havedeveloped FADN database for handling data and analysis.

title.narrative: State Veterinary Office of BiH implementing an effective animal identification and registration system

baseline.value: Animal ID only covering 50% of cattle

target.value: database up and running, randoms counter checks of 10% cattle and 3% small ruminants.

actual.value: Animal I&R in operation, need of zero baseline to be implemented.

title.narrative: SVO implementing brucellosis and CSF controlprograms

baseline.value: Brucellosis and CSFepidemiology data outdated.Limited test and slaughterprogram for Brucella

target.value: In animal health > 75% ofsmall ruminants are vaccinatedfor Brucellosis each year

actual.value: CSF study complete - results show low prevalence with possibility to erradicate. Vaccination policy maintained due to prevalence inneighboring countries.5th year in vaccination campaign for brucellosis of all small ruminants.

title.narrative: FSA implementing a risk based food safety system

baseline.value: FSA only recently established and food regulation and inspection procedures incomplete

target.value: FSA performs at least 3 risk assessments and coordinates a risk communication program

actual.value: FSA has conducted - Total diet risk assessment study, a phosphate water contamination risk assessment study, aflatoxins riskassessment study. Network of reference laboratories upgraded and tests accredited. Risk communication program in force withdissemination of reports ,television programing and heightened inspections

title.narrative: APPH develops and implements phytosanitary and plant register database

baseline.value: No centralized database for phytosanitary or plant production or trade

target.value: Link phyto-plant health registry with FSA and SVO databases and MOFTER farm information

actual.value: Phyto-plant health register operational with data entry at entity level inspection services and sharing protocol with APPH forcoordinating and information role at state level.

title.narrative: WAN linking MOFTER with state level agencies, entity MoAs and Inspection services under establishment for AIS

baseline.value: No coherent agricultural information collection at state level

target.value: Begin interface of various entity level and state agency databases for AIS

actual.value: Agreement on data protocol established with APPH and Entities Ministry of Agriculture and Entity Inspection Services. Links betweenState level agencies and inspection services established. Link with Farm and client register partially established. MOFTER equippedwith server, but links with entity services and State agencies, only partial.

title.narrative: Entity-Leval Inspection Directorates are implementing BiH plant health, animal health and food safety laws and regulations

target.value: In food safety: > 90% of food establishments are registered and > 50% are inspected, on a risk basis, yearly

actual.value: Inspection MIS system installed, link established with Plant Health Agency.

title.narrative: Structured disease and pest control system, informed by surveys and supported by reliable laboratory diagnostic capacity and databases, are developed, coordinated and implemented at all levels

baseline.value: No systematic disease and pest control system for plants, animals and food stuff in place

target.value: Monitor and report on situation trough regular reports from inspection services, to begin risk targeting of inspections

actual.value: - Livestock identification and registration system in service. Zero baseline being implemented during the course of the summer aspart of required action plan for milk exports.- Disease notification system operational- Phyto register in operation linked withinspection services in both entities- Brucellosis vaccination policy in 5th year of implementation- Classical Swine fevervaccination policy in force- Residues testing plan accepted and implemented- Action Plan agreed with EU FVO for activitiestowards meeting requirements for export of milk, eggs, and poultry under implementation- Potato survey conducted regularly andfunded by entities with export authorization to EU obtained- Inspection services in both entities implements yearly inspectionplan and reporting in IT systems

title.narrative: Registries and databases for the effective management of incentive payments, tracking of sanitary inspection data at Entity levels with reporting capacity to state level agencies and MOFTER in place

baseline.value: No systematic registry and reporting capacity in place

target.value: Develop links for various registries for Farm Information System approximating EU requirements

actual.value: - Farm and client registers operational in both Entities, partially linked with State level Coordination office to support accuratepayment of incentives at entity level- Livestock registration and identification to support accurate direct payments.- Ruraldevelopment strategies and programs available in both entities.- Registers of food operators held and managed in Ministries ofAgriculture in both entities- Policy framework for food safety implementation with risk analysis developed- Links with inspectionIT systems under development and in some cases fully functional for each database.
